This paper deals with a path-planning problem in a geometric setting, which is a classic topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem involves finding a path that satisfies certain constraints, which is a common theme in robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithmic techniques used in the paper involve approximation algorithms and optimization, which are relevant to the fields of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
